<subSubSection id="C3143EC9FFAFBB3FFF3BFCE3FBF9FCAC" pageId="8" pageNumber="209" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BB16D42FFAFBB3FFF3BFCE3FBF9FCAC" blockId="8.[151,1437,151,866]" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">
<emphasis id="B97AB150FFAFBB3FFF3BFCE3FE30FC88" bold="true" box="[199,461,769,794]" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
The shape of the cerci with their distinctive basal lobes and the distinctive vase shaped phallus serve to easily distinguish this species from other species in the genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3143EC9FFAFBB3FFF3BFCABFB2DFCF0" box="[199,1232,841,866]" pageId="8" pageNumber="209" type="etymology">
